  "prompt": "How do you factory reset an iPhone 4 without a computer?",
  "response": "To factory reset an iPhone 4 without using a computer, you can follow these steps:\n\n### **Method 1: Using the Settings App**\n1. **Backup Your Data (Optional):**\n   - If you want to save your data, back it up to iCloud before proceeding.  \n     Go to **Settings** > **iCloud** > **Backup** and tap **Back Up Now**.\n\n[\n\n2. **Erase All Content and Settings:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **General** > **Reset**.\n   - Tap **Erase All Content and Settings**.\n   - If prompted, enter your passcode or Apple ID password.\n   - Confirm the action by tapping **Erase iPhone**.\n\nThe iPhone 4 will restart and restore itself to factory settings.\n\n### **Method 2: Using Recovery Mode (If You Can\u2019t Access Settings)**\nIf you can\u2019t access the Settings app (e.g., because of a forgotten passcode), you can use Recovery Mode. However, this method typically requires a computer. If you don\u2019t have access to a computer, the first method is your only option.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes:**\n- Ensure your iPhone 4 is **charged** or connected to a power source during the process.\n- A factory reset will **erase all data**, including apps, photos, and settings, so make sure you\u2019ve backed up anything important.\n- After the reset, you\u2019ll need to set up the iPhone 4 as if it were new or restore it from a backup.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
